The paper discusses the citation process for scientific papers, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. However, the focus on the evolution of author citations and bursty dynamics suggests that the paper is most likely to belong to the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the use of a simple model to reproduce citation and burst size distributions suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Digital Libraries (cs.DL), Cybernetics (cs.CY), Information Retrieval (cs.IR), and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR).
